# {{l|en|air}} (mixture of gases that make up the earth's atmosphere)

----

==Pohnpeian==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ɐjir/|lang=pon}}

===Verb===
{{head|pon|verb}}

# {{lb|pon|transitive}} to [[strip off]], as when stripping insulation off a wire
# {{lb|pon|transitive}} to [[wipe off]] a [[ropelike]] object by [[drawing]] it through one's [[hand]] or [[fingers]]
#: {{ux|pon|'''Air''' mahs keleuen.|Please wipe the sap off the hibiscus bast.}}

----

==Scottish Gaelic==

===Etymology===
From {{der|gd|sga|for}} (compare Irish {{m|ga|ar}}), from {{der|gd|cel-pro|*uɸor}} (compare Welsh {{m|cy|ar}}), from {{der|gd|ine-pro|*upér}} (compare Latin {{m|la|super}}, Ancient Greek {{m|grc|ὑπέρ}}, Old English {{m|ang|ofer}}).

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ɛrʲ/|lang=gd}}

===Preposition===
{{head|gd|preposition}}

# [[on]], [[upon]]
#: {{ux|gd|'''air''' bàrr a' bhalla|t=on top of the wall|inline=1}}
# [[of]], [[concerning]]
#: {{ux|gd|iomradh '''air''' do ghliocas|t=a report of thy wisdom|inline=1}}
# [[for]], [[on account of]]
#: {{ux|gd|'''air''' an aobhar sin|t=for that reason|inline=1}}
# [[by]]
#: {{ux|gd|'''air''' ainm|t=by name|inline=1}}

====Usage notes====
* '''Air''' combines with personal pronouns to form prepositional pronouns. See ''Derived forms'' below. Specifically for ''air'' the third-person singular masculine pronoun is identical to the uninflected preposition, hence ''air'' = ''on'' or ''on him''.
* The word '''air''' and its derivates are also used in many idioms:
*: {{ux|gd|Dè an t-ainm a tha ort?|What's your name? (What name is '''on you'''?)|inline=1}}
*: {{ux|gd|Tha an t-acras orm.|t=I'm hungry. (The hunger is '''on me'''.)|inline=1}}

====Derived terms====
{{der3|lang=gd|{{l|gd|air dheireadh||behind; late}}
|{{l|gd|air fhichead||twenty-...}}
|{{l|gd|air sgàth||for the sake of}}
|{{l|gd|airson||for}}}}

* The following prepositional pronouns:
{{gd-prep-infl
|1sg=orm
|2sg=ort
|3sgm=air
|3sgf=oirre
|1pl=oirnn
|2pl=oirbh
|3pl=orra
}}

===Pronoun===
{{head|gd|prepositional pronoun|g=m}}

