==Dutch==

===Alternative forms===
* {{l|nl|gelove}} {{qual|archaic}}

===Etymology===
From earlier {{m|nl|gelove}}, from {{inh|nl|dum|gelove}}, from {{inh|nl|odt|gilovo}}, from {{inh|nl|gem-pro|*galaubô}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{rhymes|oːf|lang=nl}}
* {{audio|Nl-geloof.ogg|audio|lang=nl}}

===Noun===
{{nl-noun|n|-ven|geloofje}}

# [[belief]], [[conviction]].
# {{lb|nl|religion}} [[faith]], [[religion]].

====Usage notes====
The genitive form of the word is ''des geloofs''. Of its alternative form ''gelove'' it is ''des geloven'' or ''des geloves''. In Dutch, the genitive is not commonly used outside of fixed expressions and literary language, but can be frequently encountered in early modern Dutch texts.

====Synonyms====
* {{sense|belief|conviction}} {{l|nl|overtuiging}}
* {{sense|religion}} {{l|nl|godsdienst}}, {{l|nl|religie}}

====Derived terms====
* {{l|nl|bijgeloof}} {{g2|n}}
* {{l|nl|geloofsbelijdenis}}
* {{l|nl|gelovig}}

===Verb===
{{nl-verb-form}}

# {{nl-verb form of|p=1|n=sg|t=pres|m=ind|geloven}}
# {{nl-verb form of|m=imp|geloven}}

==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|lēafa}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*laubô}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/bɪˈliːf/|/bəˈliːf/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-belief.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|iːf|lang=en}}
* {{hyphenation|be|lief|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# [[mental|Mental]] [[acceptance]] of a [[claim]] as true.
#: {{ux|en|It's my '''belief''' that the thief is somebody known to us.}}
#* {{quote-magazine|date=2013-12-06|author={{w|George Monbiot}}
|volume=189|issue=26|page=48|magazine={{w|The Guardian Weekly}}
|title=[http://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2013/nov/27/al-gore-veganism-eating-words-sceptical-meat-eating Why I'm eating my words on veganism – again]
|passage=The '''belief''' that there is no conflict between [livestock] farming and arable production also seems to be unfounded: by preventing the growth of trees and other deep vegetation in the hills and by compacting the soil, grazing animals cause a cycle of flash floods and drought, sporadically drowning good land downstream and reducing the supply of irrigation water.}}
# [[Faith]] or [[trust]] in the reality of something; often based upon one's own reasoning, trust in a claim, desire of actuality, and/or evidence considered.
#: {{ux|en|My '''belief''' is that there is a bear in the woods. Bill said he saw one.}}
#: {{ux|en|Based on this data, it is our '''belief''' that X does not occur.}}
# {{lb|en|countable}} Something [[believe]]d.
#: {{ux|en|The ancient people have a '''belief''' in many deities.}}
#* {{ux|en|Women always take the '''beliefs''' of those around them. Better a man who loves her to have the strongest influence over her '''beliefs''' and actions than her catty girlfriends who despise her for being more attractive. ― Blair Naso}}
# {{lb|en|uncountable}} The quality or state of [[believe|believing]].
#: {{ux|en|My '''belief''' that it will rain tomorrow is strong.}}
# {{lb|en|uncountable}} [[religious|Religious]] [[faith]].
#: {{ux|en|She often said it was her '''belief''' that carried her through the hard times.}}
# {{lb|en|in the plural}} One's religious or [[moral]] [[convictions]].
#: {{ux|en|I don't want to do a no-fault divorce on my husband and steal from him under color of law. It's against my '''beliefs'''.}}

