===Etymology 2===
{{etyl|xno|en}} and {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|pel}} (compare modern French {{m|fr|pieu}}), from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|palus||stake}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A [[stake]].
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A fence made of stakes; a [[stockade]].
# {{lb|en|archaic}} A small [[tower]], [[fort]], or [[castle]]; a [[keep]].

=====Derived terms=====
* {{l|en|peel-house}}, {{l|en|peelhouse}}
* {{l|en|peel-tower}}

===Etymology 3===
From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|pele}} (compare modern {{m|fr|pelle}}), from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|pala}}, from the base of {{m|la|plangere||fix, plant}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A [[shovel]] or similar instrument, now especially a [[pole]] with a flat disc at the end used for removing [[pizza]] or [[loaves]] of [[bread]] from a baker's oven.
# A T-shaped implement used by [[printer]]s and [[bookbinder]]s for hanging wet sheets of [[paper]] on lines or poles to dry.
# {{lb|en|archaic|US}} The [[blade]] of an [[oar]].

