====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# To [[follow]] at somebody's heels; to [[chase]] closely.
#: {{ux|en|She called to her dog to '''heel'''.}}
# To add a heel to, or increase the size of the heel of (a shoe or boot).
# To [[kick]] with the heel.
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To perform by the use of the heels, as in dancing, running, etc.
#* William Shakespeare, ''Troilus and Cressida'' (act 4, scene 4, lines 85-86)
#*: I cannot sing, / Nor '''heel''' the high lavolt.
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[arm]] with a [[gaff]], as a [[cock]] for [[fight]]ing.
# {{lb|en|golf|transitive}} To hit (the ball) with the heel of the club.
# {{lb|en|American football|transitive}} To make (a fair catch) standing with one foot forward, the heel on the ground and the toe up.

